25/07/2003
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- One person was killed and four were injured when grenades were thrown at the UN police headquarters in Mitrovica late Thursday (24 July) night. Two of the wounded are in critical condition. UN spokesman Andrea Angeli says no UN personnel were among the casualties. Two suspects were taken into custody. (AP, Reuters, AFP, BBC, B92, Montenegrin Radio - 24/07/03)
